    <main>
        <section id="ecosystem-services" class="project-detail">
            <div class="container project-flex">
                <div class="project-image">
                    <img src="images/Campo.jpg" alt="Field Work">
                </div>
                <div class="project-text">
                    <span class="project-tag">Ecosystem Services</span>
                    <h2>Weed seed predation by rodents</h2>
                    <p>This project explores how native and exotic rodents contribute to weed control in agroecosystems of central Argentina. We focus on herbicide-resistant species and how landscape configuration affects predation rates.</p>
                    <div class="results-box">
                        <strong>Key Results:</strong> Predation is higher in field borders compared to the center, suggesting that maintaining natural vegetation can enhance this ecosystem service.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="foraging-preferences" class="project-detail">
            <div class="container project-flex reverse">
                <div class="project-image">
                    <img src="images/Bioterio.jpg" alt="Lab Research">
                </div>
                <div class="project-text">
                    <span class="project-tag">Foraging preferences</span>
                    <h2>Seed traits and rodent choices</h2>
                    <p>By conducting controlled experiments, we analyze how seed size, nutritional content, and chemical defenses influence the choices of different rodent species.</p>
                    <div class="results-box">
                        <strong>Key Results:</strong> Seed size is a primary driver for selection, but high protein content can override size preferences in certain seasonal contexts.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="environmental-change" class="project-detail">
            <div class="container project-flex">
                <div class="project-image">
                    <img src="images/Mus_city.png" alt="Urban Ecology">
                </div>
                <div class="project-text">
                    <span class="project-tag">Environmental change</span>
                    <h2>Urban occupancy of <i>Mus musculus</i></h2>
                    <p>We modeled the presence of the house mouse in expanding cities, considering urban growth patterns and socio-environmental variables.</p>
                    <div class="results-box">
                        <strong>Key Results:</strong> House mouse occupancy is strongly linked to the age of the urban sector and the density of built-up areas.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
